<HEADLINE>Row over Enterprise cut grows</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974880835</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE row over the Scottish Enterprise budget cut grew last night with an angry
exchange of letters between Labour's George Robertson and Scottish Secretary
Michael Forsyth.
Mr Robertson said he had found it astonishing that the Scottish Enterprise
chairman ``should be practically volunteering cuts in his own budget.''
It showed the extent ``to which Michael Forsyth will exploit his quango empire
towards his own political ends.''
Mr Forsyth replied he had been assured that the organisation could live with a
7.5% cut ``and yet maintain or improve output through increased efficiencies.''
He described as ``singularly inappropriate'' Mr Robertson's criticism of the
Scottish Enterprise chairman.
</TEXT>
