<TEXT>
NAIRN County, second bottom in the Highland League, are launching a team video
as part of efforts to set the club back on a firm financial footing. For #5,
fans can relive classic County action from this season. The team have so far
conceded 44 goals in 15 league outings.
Boy missing
POLICE in Inverness yesterday appealed for information about 15-year-old
Kenneth MacLeod, who went missing from near the gates of his school, Millburn
Academy, at around 8.20am on Wednesday. He is 5ft 10in, slim, and has dark,
wavy hair.
Out of luck
A MAN found with 460 stolen National Lottery scratchcards was fined #200 for
reset at Inverness Sheriff Court yesterday. Andrew Russell, 37, had two bin
bags containing the cards at his home in MacKay Road, Inverness.
Bookie a loser
A SEARCH is on in Inverness for a three-wheeler that isn't a Reliant Robin
after a car wheel smashed through the window of a Ladbroke's betting shop in
Lochalsh Road.
</TEXT>
