<DOCID>GH951215-000073</DOCID>
<DATE>951215</DATE>
<HEADLINE>MAINTENANCE Danes clean up</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>20</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974880853</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
EDINBURGH-based cleaning company Northern Maintenance has been acquired by
Copenhagen based ISS for more than #1m.
The acquisition gives international cleaning and support services group ISS its
first major foothold in Scotland.
Northern, with an annual turnover of more than #3m and 900 employees, is one of
the leading independent cleaning and maintenance companies north of the Border.
Operations director Bruce Cochrane will remain with the company under ISS and
will head the Danish company's operations in Scotland.
Bill Buchanan, Northern's managing director, is retiring.
ISS said last night that it intended to keep Northern intact.
</TEXT>
