THE Scottish Open Championships look set to lose their grand-prix status - in
the same year as Scotland hosts the World Championships for the first time. The
International Badminton Federation have ruled that all tournaments seeking
grand-prix status must have a prize fund of at least $30,000 from 1997. Last
month's Scottish Open had prize money of only $15,000.
