<DATE>951215</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Hetherston is set to go</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>37</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974880907</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ABERDEEN have put midfield player Peter Hetherston on the transfer list.
Pittodrie manager Roy Aitken, who will want to recoup the #200,000 paid to
Raith Rovers for Hetherston last season, said: ``He never moved his family up
here which has proved a burden and affected his form. I have come to the
conclusion that it is in the interests of both parties to make him available
for transfer.''
``Peter has done a great job here and I am sure he can still fill a major role
with another club.''
However, one man with no thoughts of leaving Pittodrie is Joe Miller, who is
convinced the club will avert an exodus of top players and build on their
Coca-Cola Cup success.
The winger is one of seven Aberdeen players out of contract at the end of the
season. But he said yesterday: ``No-one is in a hurry to leave. It is obvious
that exciting times lie ahead under Roy Aitken. We have just won a cup and have
the makings of a very good team.
``I'm sure the club will sort out the contract situation in plenty of time. I
would be happy to stay. For the most part I have been a first-team regular
under the manager and that is all I've ever wanted.
``Scoring the hat trick against Kilmarnock was a welcome change. In recent
weeks I have been trying too hard and it never happened for me.
``It has been frustrating but throughout my career I have been able to get
among the goals. That's seven now and I will be aiming to get into double
figures as soon as possible.''
Captain Stewart McKimmie, Eoin Jess, Gary Smith, Brian Grant, and keepers Theo
Snelders and Michael Watt are all out of contract at the end of the season.
</TEXT>
