<DOCNO>GH951215-000120</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951215-000120</DOCID>
<DATE>951215</DATE>
<HEADLINE>County in the picture</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>37</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974880912</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
IT sounds like a form of masochism but Nairn County are about to issue a video
of their performances so far this season.
For just #5, County supporters can sit through the highlights - if indeed that
is the right word - of some of their side's 15 league games, during which they
have conceeded 44 goals, and been successful just three times. Sounds like fun,
doesn't it.
The man to ``blame'' is local businessman and camaraman Charlie Robertson, who
is sure the tape will prove a popular stocking filler with Nairn supporters at
Christmas.
But hold on, it would be pointless charging down to your local video store
right away with your fiver in hand because Charlie's classic will not be
available at leading stores - it could frighten the children.
An initial run of 20 tapes are up for grabs at Nairn's social club Christmas
fayre. Freddy Kreuger, eat your heart out.
</TEXT>
